name: ad-hene

attributes.attribute: called their neighbors in the ghostly Otherworld by euphemisms such as this one, which means simply “Themselves.”

attributes.entity: Residents of the Isle of Man
attributes.attribute: called their neighbors in the ghostly Otherworld by euphemisms such as ad-hene Manx spirits.

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.
text: Manx spirits, much like their counterparts in other Celtic territories, were referred to by the inhabitants of the Isle of Man using polite expressions, such as “Themselves.” This term was employed to denote residents of the ghostly Otherworld. For more information, consult the section on Names For The Fairies.
